ereen.essos.local \n```\n\nWorks as expected when a user is provided:\n```\nnxc smb meereen.essos.local -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' -M nopac\nSMB         192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:MEEREEN) (domain:essos.local) (signing:True) (SMBv1:True) (Null Auth:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          [+] essos.local\\khal.drogo:horse \nNOPAC       192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          TGT with PAC size 1465\nNOPAC       192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          TGT without PAC size 708\nNOPAC       192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          \nNOPAC       192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          VULNERABLE\nNOPAC       192.168.56.12   445    MEEREEN          Next step: https://github.com/Ridter/noPac\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nError without a stacktrace.\n\n**NetExec info**\n - OS: Kali\n - Version of nxc: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816\n - Installed from: pipx\n\n", "hints_text": "This should definitely be caught and if the file doesn't exist we should exit the entire program\n\nThis is because the SAMR/LSA functions don't support hash authentication right now, we'll have to update that. Eventually should probably move them to better areas (LSA to its own) and improve the object initialization as well.\n\n\n\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "This should definitely be caught and if the file doesn't exist we should exit the entire program\n\nThis is because the SAMR/LSA functions don't support hash authentication right now, we'll have to update that. Eventually should probably move them to better areas (LSA to its own) and improve the object initialization as well.\n\n\n\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/86bf9d446d8ed3dfe29c6c0e1042e534b174e12a", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/0bfa8fb3b593645349ed1692d8bc2cb70ebb384d", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/67ddd28ba2dd3bd25fb742cb8faeda2221ac1b11", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/a87143d27ffda9e2ec5d7732deeb00e6441c4496"], "created_at": "2025-11-13T11:39:48Z"}
{"repo": "Pennyw0rth/NetExec", "pull_number": 911, "instance_id": "Pennyw0rth__NetExec-911", "issue_numbers": [870], "base_commit": "c13aba6a24bdc6ca1bb2229078141818f2e4ac74", "patch": "diff --git a/nxc/protocols/ldap.py b/nxc/protocols/ldap.py\nindex 2cb3924dc2..be9077bb25 100644\n--- a/nxc/protocols/ldap.py\n+++ b/nxc/protocols/ldap.py\n@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@\n import hashlib\n import hmac\n import os\n+import socket\n from errno import EHOSTUNREACH, ETIMEDOUT, ENETUNREACH\n from binascii import hexlify\n from datetime import datetime\n@@ -830,7 +831,8 @@ def computers(self):\n     def dc_list(self):\n         # bypass host resolver configuration via configure=False (default pulls from /etc/resolv.conf or registry on Windows)\n         resolv = resolver.Resolver(configure=False)\n-        resolv.nameservers = [self.args.dns_server] if self.args.dns_server else [self.host]\n+        ns = self.args.dns_server or self.host\n+        resolv.nameservers = [socket.gethostbyname(ns)]\n         self.logger.debug(f\"DNS Server option: {self.args.dns_server}, using DNS server: {resolv.nameservers}\")\n         resolv.timeout = self.args.dns_timeout\n \n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/e2e_commands.txt b/tests/e2e_commands.txt\nindex 3c751959f0..4005ff378a 100644\n--- a/tests/e2e_commands.txt\n+++ b/tests/e2e_commands.txt\n@@ -204,6 +204,7 @@ netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS --admin-co\n netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS --gmsa\n netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS --pso\n netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS --pass-pol\n+netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS --dc-list\n ##### LDAP Modules\n netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS -L\n netexec ldap TARGET_HOST -u LOGIN_USERNAME -p LOGIN_PASSWORD KERBEROS -M adcs\n", "problem_statement": "--dc-list error \"nameserver is not a dns.nameserver.Nameserver instance or text form, IP address, nor a valid https URL\"\n**Describe the bug**\nThe error `nameserver dc.voleur.htb is not a dns.nameserver.Nameserver instance or text form, IP address, nor a valid https URL` is thrown when running `--dc-list`.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nRunning `--dc-list` on the Voleur HTB machine results in:\n```\nnxc --dns-timeout 5 ldap dc.voleur.htb -u 'ryan.naylor' -p 'HollowOct31Nyt' -k --dc-list --verbose \n[21:32:32] INFO     Socket info: host=dc.voleur.htb, hostname=dc.voleur.htb, kerberos=True, ipv6=False, link-local ipv6=False                                                                                      connection.py:177\n           INFO     Connecting to ldap://dc.voleur.htb with no baseDN                                                                                                                                                    ldap.py:180\n[21:32:33] INFO     Resolved domain: voleur.htb with dns, kdcHost: 10.10.11.76                                                                                                                                           ldap.py:325\nLDAP        dc.voleur.htb   389    DC               [*] None (name:DC) (domain:voleur.htb) (signing:None) (channel binding:No TLS cert) (NTLM:False)\n           INFO     Connecting to ldap://DC.voleur.htb - DC=voleur,DC=htb - dc.voleur.htb [1]                                                                                                                            ldap.py:389\nLDAP        dc.voleur.htb   389    DC               [+] voleur.htb\\ryan.naylor:HollowOct31Nyt \n[21:32:34] ERROR    Exception while calling proto_flow() on target dc.voleur.htb: nameserver dc.voleur.htb is not a dns.nameserver.Nameserver instance or text form, IP address, nor a valid https URL             connection.py:188\n                    \u256d\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u