unning `nxc --dns-timeout 5 ldap dc.voleur.htb -u 'ryan.naylor' -p 'HollowOct31Nyt' -k --dc-list --verbose` still gives the error.\n\nBut using `--dns-server` flag resolves the issue:\n```\nnxc --dns-timeout 5 ldap dc.voleur.htb -u 'ryan.naylor' -p 'HollowOct31Nyt' -k --dc-list --verbose --dns-server 10.10.11.76   \n[17:38:31] INFO     Socket info: host=dc.voleur.htb, hostname=dc.voleur.htb, kerberos=True, ipv6=False, link-local ipv6=False                                                                                                                                                                      connection.py:177\n           INFO     Connecting to ldap://dc.voleur.htb with no baseDN                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    ldap.py:180\n[17:38:32] INFO     Resolved domain: voleur.htb with dns, kdcHost: 10.10.11.76                                                                                                                                                                                                                           ldap.py:325\nLDAP        dc.voleur.htb   389    DC               [*] None (name:DC) (domain:voleur.htb) (signing:None) (channel binding:No TLS cert) (NTLM:False)\n           INFO     Connecting to ldap://DC.voleur.htb - DC=voleur,DC=htb - dc.voleur.htb [1]                                                                                                                                                                                                            ldap.py:389\nLDAP        dc.voleur.htb   389    DC               [+] voleur.htb\\ryan.naylor:HollowOct31Nyt \n[17:38:33] INFO     Enumerating Domain Controllers in current domain...                                                                                                                            