02   resolv = resolver.Resolver()                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    824 \u2502   \u2502   if self.args.dns_server:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    825 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   resolv.nameservers = [self.args.dns_server]                                                                                                                                                                                                             \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    826 \u2502   \u2502   else:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       \u2502                  \n                    \u2502                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u2502                  \n                    \u2502 /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/dns/resolver.py:945 in __init__                                                                                                                                                                      \u2502                  \n                    \u2502                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    942 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   if sys.platform == \"win32\":  # pragma: no cover                                                                                                                                                                                                         \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    943 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   self.read_registry()                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    944 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   elif filename:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \u2502                  \n                    \u2502 \u2771  945 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   self.read_resolv_conf(filename)                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    946 \u2502                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    947 \u2502   def reset(self) -> None:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \u2502                  \n                    \u2502    948 \u2502   \u2502   \"\"\"Reset all resolver configuration to the defaults.\"\"\"                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u2502                  \n                    \u2502                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u2502                  \n                    \u2502 /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/dns/resolver.py:1039 in read_resolv_conf                                                                                                                                                             \u2502                  \n                    \u2502                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u2502                  \n                    \u2502   1036 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   except (ValueError, IndexError):                                                                                                                                                                                                        \u2502                  \n                    \u2502   1037 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   pass                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \u2502                  \n                    \u2502   1038 \u2502   \u2502   if len(nameservers) == 0:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   \u2502                  \n                    \u2502 \u2771 1039 \u2502   \u2502   \u2502   raise NoResolverConfiguration(\"no nameservers\")                                                                                                                                                                                                         \u2502                  \n                    \u2502   1040 \u2502   \u2502   # Assigning directly instead of appending means we invoke the                                                                                                                                                                                               \u2502                  \n                    \u2502   1041 \u2502   \u2502   # setter logic, with additonal checking and enrichment.                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u2502                  \n                    \u2502   1042 \u2502   \u2502   self.nameservers = nameservers                                                                                                                                                                                                                              \u2502                  \n                    \u2570\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256f                  \n                    NoResolverConfiguration: no nameservers\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nList of domain controllers is shown.\n\n**NetExec info**\n - OS: Kali\n - Version of nxc: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816\n - Installed from: pipx\n\n", "hints_text": "Thanks for the report. We can definitely catch this error, but this works fine for me in my GOAD environment. Is your DNS properly set? It looks like it is not, which is causing this and maybe #870\nMy output looks like this (note I am using .55.x instead of .56.x):\n\n```\n[netexec-PEBb9Hvh-py3.13]-> nxc ldap 192.168.55.12 -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' --dc-list --verbose\n[09:32:00] INFO     Socket info: host=192.168.55.12, hostname=192.168.55.12, kerberos=False, ipv6=False, link-local ipv6=False                                                                                                                                                                 connection.py:177\n           INFO     Connecting to ldap://192.168.55.12 with no baseDN                                                                                                                                                                                                                                ldap.py:180\n[09:32:10] INFO     Error resolving hostname essos.local: [Errno -2] Name or service not known                                                                                                                                                                                                 connection.py:204\n           INFO     Resolved domain: essos.local with dns, kdcHost: None                                                                                                                                                                                                                             ldap.py:325\nLDAP        192.168.55.12   389    MEEREEN          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 (name:MEEREEN) (domain:essos.local) (signing:None) (channel binding:Never) \n           INFO     Connecting to ldap://meereen.essos.local - DC=essos,DC=local - 192.168.55.12 [3]                                                                                                                                                                                                 ldap.py:510\nLDAP        192.168.55.12   389    MEEREEN          [+] essos.local\\khal.drogo:horse \n[09:32:11] INFO     Enumerating Domain Controllers in current domain...                                                                                                                                                                                                                              ldap.py:864\nLDAP        192.168.55.12   389    MEEREEN          meereen.essos.local = 192.168.55.12\n           INFO     Enumerating Trusted Domains...                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   ldap.py:875\n           INFO     Processing trusted domain: sevenkingdoms.local (SEVENKINGDOMS)                                                                                                                                                                                                                   ldap.py:926\n           INFO     Trust type: Active Directory, Direction: Bidirectional, Trust Attributes: Forest Transitive                                                                                                                                                                                      ldap.py:927\n           INFO     Found domain controllers for trusted domain sevenkingdoms.local via DNS:                                                                                                                                                                                                         ldap.py:939\nLDAP        192.168.55.12   389    MEEREEN          [+] Found DC in trusted domain: kingslanding.sevenkingdoms.local\nLDAP        192.168.55.12   389    MEEREEN          sevenkingdoms.local -> Bidirectional -> Forest Transitive\nLDAP        192.168.55.12   389    MEEREEN          kingslanding.sevenkingdoms.local = 192.168.55.10\n           INFO     Domain Controller enumeration complete.\n```\n\nI am also using a local dnsmasq server with the following config to point DNS resolution for GOAD to the proper DNS server (.10):\n\n```\nserver=/north.sevenkingdoms.local/192.168.55.10\nserver=/sevenkingdoms.local/192.168.55.10\nserver=/essos.local/192.168.55.10\nserver=/55.168.192.in-addr.arpa/192.168.55.10\n```\n\nif you set `--dns-server 192.168.56.10`, does that fix this issue?\nI did have my `/etc/hosts` setup wrong. I changed my hosts file to match what Mayfly sets it to [here](https://mayfly277.github.io/posts/GOADv2-pwning_part1/):\n\n```\n192.168.56.10   sevenkingdoms.local kingslanding.sevenkingdoms.local kingslanding\n192.168.56.11   winterfell.north.sevenkingdoms.local north.sevenkingdoms.local winterfell\n192.168.56.12   essos.local meereen.essos.local meereen\n192.168.56.22   castelblack.north.sevenkingdoms.local castelblack\n192.168.56.23   braavos.essos.local braavos\n```\n\nBut I still get the same stacktrace after correcting it and rebooting.\n\nSetting `--dns-server` also doesn't resolve the issue: `nxc ldap 192.168.56.12 -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' --dc-list --verbose --dns-server 192.168.56.10`\n@seihtam can you post the full `--debug` output with the dns-server command?\n```\nnxc ldap 192.168.56.12 -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' --dc-list --dns-server 192.168.56.10 --debug\n[16:19:23] DEBUG    NXC VERSION: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816                                                                                                                                                                                                                               netexec.py:82\n           DEBUG    PYTHON VERSION: 3.13.3 (main, Apr 10 2025, 21:38:51) [GCC 14.2.0]                                                                                                                                                                                                                  netexec.py:83\n           DEBUG    RUNNING ON: Linux Rele