00\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256f                  \n                    OSError: [Errno 9] Bad file descriptor                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n[12:09:16] DEBUG    Closing connection to: meereen.essos.local   \n```\n\nWhen changing the order of the modules no error is shown:\n```\nnxc ldap meereen.essos.local -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' -M adcs -M pre2k\nLDAP        192.168.56.12   389    MEEREEN          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 (name:MEEREEN) (domain:essos.local) (signing:None) (channel binding:Never) \nLDAP        192.168.56.12   389    MEEREEN          [+] essos.local\\khal.drogo:horse \nADCS        192.168.56.12   389    MEEREEN          [*] Starting LDAP search with search filter '(objectClass=pKIEnrollmentService)'\nADCS        192.168.56.12   389    MEEREEN          Found PKI Enrollment Server: braavos.essos.local\nADCS        192.168.56.12   389    MEEREEN          Found CN: ESSOS-CA\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nModules should run normally.\n\n**NetExec info**\n - OS: Kali\n - Version of nxc: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816\n - Installed from: pipx\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/fa27fa793be268d02703e11392c405008b92d358", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/915a68395a550fa8dac9ce65f503831a0c9e75e9", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/a050a59eabbc1a9a6404763b2c5718f08ec35896"], "created_at": "2025-08-24T16:33:12Z"}
{"repo": "Pennyw0rth/NetExec", "pull_number": 914, "instance_id": "Pennyw0rth__NetExec-914", "issue_numbers": [880], "base_commit": "d0ea79a199464ffef6627aa08f4f4859eec71173", "patch": "diff --git a/nxc/modules/webdav.py b/nxc/modules/webdav.py\nindex b017fe738a..29738d9f77 100644\n--- a/nxc/modules/webdav.py\n+++ b/nxc/modules/webdav.py\n@@ -3,6 +3,8 @@\n from impacket import nt_errors\n from impacket.smb3structs import FILE_READ_DATA\n from impacket.smbconnection import SessionError\n+from impacket.nmb import NetBIOSError\n+import contextlib\n \n \n class NXCModule:\n@@ -11,6 +13,7 @@ class NXCModule:\n     DAV RPC Service pipe. This technique was first suggested by Lee Christensen (@tifkin_)\n \n     Module by Tobias Neitzel (@qtc_de)\n+    Modified by @azoxlpf to handle transport errors gracefully and avoid session crash\n     \"\"\"\n \n     name = \"webdav\"\n@@ -32,16 +35,18 @@ def on_login(self, context, connection):\n         \"\"\"\n         try:\n             remote_file = RemoteFile(connection.conn, \"DAV RPC Service\", \"IPC$\", access=FILE_READ_DATA)\n-\n             remote_file.open_file()\n-            remote_file.close()\n \n             context.log.highlight(self.output.format(connection.conn.getRemoteHost()))\n-\n         except SessionError as e:\n             if e.getErrorCode() == nt_errors.STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND:\n-                pass\n+                return\n             elif e.getErrorCode() in nt_errors.ERROR_MESSAGES:\n                 context.log.fail(f\"Error enumerating WebDAV: {e.getErrorString()[0]}\", color=\"magenta\")\n             else:\n-                raise e\n+                context.log.debug(f\"WebDAV SessionError (code={hex(e.getErrorCode())})\")\n+        except (BrokenPipeError, ConnectionResetError, NetBIOSError, OSError) as e:\n+            context.log.debug(f\"WebDAV check aborted due to transport error: {e.__class__.__name__}: {e}\")\n+        finally:\n+            with contextlib.suppress(Exception):\n+                remote_file.close()\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Running enum_av module before webdav module using a null session causes \"Broken pipe\"\n**Describe the bug**\nRunning the `enum_av` module and the `webdav` module together using `-M enum_av -M webdav` over a null session causes a \"Broken pipe\" error. Switching them around and running `-M webdav -M enum_av` doesn't cause the error.\n\nThe error doesn't happen if a valid user is specified.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nRunning the modules individually and with `-M webdav -M enum_av` doesn't crash:\n```\nnxc smb BRAAVOS.essos.local -u '' -p '' -M webdav           \nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED \n[13:46:32] ERROR    NetBIOSError on target BRAAVOS.essos.local: Error occurs while reading from remote(104) \n\nnxc smb BRAAVOS.essos.local -u '' -p '' -M enum_av          \nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED \nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] SMB SessionError: code: 0xc0000022 - STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED - {Access Denied} A process has requested access to an object but has not been granted those access rights.\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] Error occurs while reading from remote(104)\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Found NOTHING!\n\nnxc smb BRAAVOS.essos.local -u '' -p '' -M webdav -M enum_av        \nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED \n[13:46:11] ERROR    NetBIOSError on target BRAAVOS.essos.local: Error occurs while reading from remote(104) \n```\n\nAlthough it does fail with `Error occurs while reading from remote(104)` probably because we are using a null session. Maybe that error could be more specific.\n\n\nRunning `-M enum_av -M webdav` with null session causes the stacktrace:\n```\nnxc smb BRAAVOS.essos.local -u '' -p '' -M enum_av -M webdav --debug\n[12:25:35] DEBUG    NXC VERSION: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816                                                                                                                                                                                                                               netexec.py:82\n           DEBUG    PYTHON VERSION: 3.13.3 (main, Apr 10 2025, 21:38:51) [GCC 14.2.0]                                                                                                                                                                                                                  netexec.py:83\n           DEBUG    RUNNING ON: Linux Release: 6.12.25-amd64                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           netexec.py:84\n           DEBUG    Passed args: Namespace(version=False, threads=256, timeout=None, jitter=None, verbose=False, debug=True, no_progress=False, log=None, force_ipv6=False, dns_server=None, dns_tcp=False, dns_timeout=3, protocol='smb', target=['BRAAVOS.essos.local'], username=[''],              netexec.py:85\n                    password=[''], cred_id=[], ignore_pw_decoding=False, no_bruteforce=False, continue_on_success=False, gfail_limit=None, ufail_limit=None, fail_limit=None, kerberos=False, use_kcache=False, aesKey=None, kdcHost=None, pfx_cert=None, pfx_base64=None, pfx_pass=None,  