500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256f                  \n                    BrokenPipeError: [Errno 32] Broken pipe                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n           DEBUG    Closing connection to: BRAAVOS.essos.local  \n```\n\nIt doesn't happen when specifying a user:\n```\nnxc smb BRAAVOS.essos.local -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' -M enum_av -M webdav\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [+] essos.local\\khal.drogo:horse (Pwn3d!)\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Found Windows Defender INSTALLED\n```\n\nIt doesn't happen when running for example `-M spooler` after `-M enum_av`:\n```\nnxc smb BRAAVOS.essos.local -u '' -p '' -M enum_av -M spooler\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED \nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] SMB SessionError: code: 0xc0000022 - STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED - {Access Denied} A process has requested access to an object but has not been granted those access rights.\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] Error occurs while reading from remote(104)\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Found NOTHING!\nSPOOLER     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Spooler service enabled\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nModules should run normally or gracefully exit.\n\n**NetExec info**\n - OS: Kali\n - Version of nxc: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816\n - Installed from: pipx\n\n", "hints_text": "My guess is that this is a problem in impacket\n\n", "all_hints_text": "My guess is that this is a problem in impacket\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/d2f6a33587a71163858fdf637bc99a4b10728f35", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/e3ef313e349441b881d2205d641f7d0870268a8c", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/7b3debabab1aee1a152bb0a902736ccc97f7db1e", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/074309f2f2103cc57233783de113e05a75e2fee6", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/d4b91f72ed118b7b6fae8bcd96384815355904bf"], "created_at": "2025-09-04T09:27:51Z"}
{"repo": "Pennyw0rth/NetExec", "pull_number": 887, "instance_id": "Pennyw0rth__NetExec-887", "issue_numbers": [881], "base_commit": "da4a846f7f2a28603866179bf4e40861f12cc593", "patch": "diff --git a/nxc/modules/enum_ca.py b/nxc/modules/enum_ca.py\nindex 6add6209cf..501c6ac547 100644\n--- a/nxc/modules/enum_ca.py\n+++ b/nxc/modules/enum_ca.py\n@@ -32,7 +32,7 @@ def __init__(self, context=None, module_options=None):\n         self.module_options = module_options\n \n     def options(self, context, module_options):\n-        pass\n+        \"\"\"No options available\"\"\"\n \n     def on_login(self, context, connection):\n         self.__username = connection.username\n@@ -80,7 +80,8 @@ def on_login(self, context, connection):\n                RPC_PROXY_CONN_A1_0X6BA_ERR in error_text:\n                 context.log.fail(\"This usually means the target does not allow \"\n                                  \"to connect to its epmapper using RpcProxy.\")\n-                return\n+            return\n+\n         for entry in entries:\n             tmpUUID = str(entry[\"tower\"][\"Floors\"][0])\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "enum_ca module causes \"UnboundLocalError\" when run against Samba server\n**Describe the bug**\nThe enum_ca module crashes with \"UnboundLocalError\" when run against a Samba server. It happens both when specifying credentials and using a null session.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSetup a Samba server:\n```\nname=\"exampleshare\"\npassword=\"exampleshare\"\n\n# Install Samba\nsudo apt update -q\nsudo apt install -yq samba\n\n# Add Samba config\necho \"\" | sudo tee -a /etc/samba/smb.conf\necho \"[$name]\" | sudo tee -a /etc/samba/smb.conf\necho \"path = $HOME/$name\" | sudo tee -a /etc/samba/smb.conf\necho \"browseable = yes\" | sudo tee -a /etc/samba/smb.conf\necho \"read only = no\" | sudo tee -a /etc/samba/smb.conf\n\n# Create smb password for current user\n(echo \"$password\"; echo \"$password\") | sudo smbpasswd -a -s $USER\n\n# Make share folder\nmkdir -p \"$HOME/$name\"\nsudo chmod -R 2770 \"$HOME/$name\"\n\n# Start Samba server\nsudo systemctl start --now smbd\n```\n\nRun `enum_ca` module against Samba server to causes crash:\n```\nnxc smb 127.0.0.1 -u '' -p '' -M enum_ca --debug\n[14:17:55] DEBUG    NXC VERSION: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816                                                                                                                                                                                                                               netexec.py:82\n           DEBUG    PYTHON VERSION: 3.13.3 (main, Apr 10 2025, 21:38:51) [GCC 14.2.0]                                                                                                                                                                                                                  netexec.py:83\n           DEBUG    RUNNING ON: Linux Release: 6.12.25-amd64                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           netexec.py:84\n           DEBUG    Passed args: Namespace(version=False, threads=256, timeout=None, jitter=None, verbose=False, debug=True, no_progress=False, log=None, force_ipv6=False, dns_server=None, dns_tcp=False, dns_timeout=3, protocol='smb', target=['127.0.0.1'], username=[''], password=[''],         netexec.py:85\n                    cred_id=[], ignore_pw_decoding=False, no_bruteforce=False, continue_on_success=False, gfail_limit=None, ufail_limit=None, fail_limit=None, kerberos=False, use_kcache=False, aesKey=None, kdcHost=None, pfx_cert=None, pfx_base64=None, pfx_pass=None, pem_cert=None,                           \n                    pem_key=None, module=['enum_ca'], module_options=[], list_modules=False, show_module_options=False, hash=[], delegate=None, no_s4u2proxy=False, domain=None, local_auth=False, port=445, share='C$', smb_server_port=445, no_smbv1=False, gen_relay_list=None, smb_timeout=2,                   \n                    laps=None, generate_hosts_file=None, generate_krb5_file=None, generate_tgt=None, sam=None, lsa=None, ntds=None, dpapi=None, sccm=None, mkfile=None, pvk=None, enabled=False, userntds=None, shares=None, dir=None, interfaces=False, no_write_check=False, filter_shares=None,                  \n                    disks=False, users=None, users_export=None, groups=None, local_groups=None, computers=None, pass_pol=False, rid_brute=None, smb_sessions=False, reg_sessions=None, loggedon_users=None, loggedon_users_filter=None, qwinsta=None, tasklist=None, taskkill=None, wmi=None,                       \n                    wmi_namespace='root\\\\cimv2', spider=None, spider_folder='.', content=False, exclude_dirs='', depth=None, only_files=False, silent=False, pattern=None, regex=None, put_file=None, get_file=None, append_host=False, exec_method='wmiexec', dcom_timeout=5, get_output_tries=100,                \n                    codec='utf-8', no_output=False, execute=None, ps_execute=None, obfs=False, amsi_bypass=None, clear_obfscripts=False, force_ps32=False, no_encode=False)                                                                                                                                         \n           DEBUG    Protocol: smb                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     netexec.py:138\n           DEBUG    Protocol Path: /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/nxc/protocols/smb.py                                                                                                                                                                         netexec.py:141\n           DEBUG    Protocol