\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256f                  \n                    UnboundLocalError: cannot access local variable 'entries' where it is not associated with a value                                                                                                                                                                                               \n           DEBUG    Closing connection to: 127.0.0.1   \n```\n\nSame thing happens if specifying credentials: `nxc smb 127.0.0.1 -u 'exampleshare' -p 'exampleshare' -M enum_ca`\n\n**Expected behavior**\nSince it's a Samba server I don't expect `enum_ca` to work, but it should error out gracefully.\n\n**NetExec info**\n - OS: Kali\n - Version of nxc: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816\n - Installed from: pipx\n\n", "hints_text": "I already had a Ubuntu server with Samba setup so I was able to confirm this. It's another classic \"not returning correctly when you need to\" issue.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I already had a Ubuntu server with Samba setup so I was able to confirm this. It's another classic \"not returning correctly when you need to\" issue.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/c5bb5a26928b0e4449c2971ba7395340f68f8219", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/1fe22400188ea825b157aaa2d6b5f7350c8ecd0b", "https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/011fc0d9dd6936e6ef0be7389e423a8f8dbb54a3"], "created_at": "2025-08-21T15:39:59Z"}
{"repo": "Pennyw0rth/NetExec", "pull_number": 884, "instance_id": "Pennyw0rth__NetExec-884", "issue_numbers": [882], "base_commit": "8af4bfa626e621882450b213ffa8de05393e2dca", "patch": "diff --git a/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py b/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py\nindex 7cc61f2c70..ff2d25be1d 100644\n--- a/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py\n+++ b/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py\n@@ -1,4 +1,3 @@\n-import sys\n from impacket import system_errors\n from impacket.dcerpc.v5.rpcrt import DCERPCException, RPC_C_AUTHN_GSS_NEGOTIATE, rpc_status_codes\n from impacket.structure import Structure\n@@ -67,7 +66,7 @@ def on_login(self, context, connection):\n             dce.bind(rprn.MSRPC_UUID_RPRN)\n         except Exception as e:\n             context.log.fail(f\"Failed to bind: {e}\")\n-            sys.exit(1)\n+            return False\n \n         flags = APD_COPY_ALL_FILES | APD_COPY_FROM_DIRECTORY | APD_INSTALL_WARNED_DRIVER\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Modules specified after the printnightmare module doesn't run if printnightmare fails\n**Describe the bug**\nModules specified after `printnightmare` on the command line doesn't run if `printnightmare` fails.\n\n**To Reproduce**\n\nRunning `-M enum_ca -M printnightmare` works as expected:\n```\nnxc smb 192.168.56.23 -u '' -p '' -M enum_ca -M printnightmare\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED \nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Active Directory Certificate Services Found.\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          http://192.168.56.23/certsrv/certfnsh.asp\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Web enrollment found on HTTP (ESC8).\nPRINTNIG... 192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] Failed to bind: SMB SessionError: code: 0xc0000022 - STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED - {Access Denied} A process has requested access to an object but has not been granted those access rights.\n```\n\nRunning `-M printnightmare -M enum_ca` causes modules specified after `-M printnightmare` on the command line to be skipped:\n```\nnxc smb 192.168.56.23 -u '' -p '' -M printnightmare -M enum_ca --debug\n[15:09:49] DEBUG    NXC VERSION: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816                                                                                                                                                                                                                               netexec.py:82\n           DEBUG    PYTHON VERSION: 3.13.3 (main, Apr 10 2025, 21:38:51) [GCC 14.2.0]                                                                                                                                                                                                                  netexec.py:83\n           DEBUG    RUNNING ON: Linux Release: 6.12.25-amd64                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           netexec.py:84\n           DEBUG    Passed args: Namespace(version=False, threads=256, timeout=None, jitter=None, verbose=False, debug=True, no_progress=False, log=None, force_ipv6=False, dns_server=None, dns_tcp=False, dns_timeout=3, protocol='smb', target=['192.168.56.23'], username=[''], password=[''],     netexec.py:85\n                    cred_id=[], ignore_pw_decoding=False, no_bruteforce=False, continue_on_success=False, gfail_limit=None, ufail_limit=None, fail_limit=None, kerberos=False, use_kcache=False, aesKey=None, kdcHost=None, pfx_cert=None, pfx_base64=None, pfx_pass=None, pem_cert=None,                           \n                    pem_key=None, module=['printnightmare', 'enum_ca'], module_options=[], list_modules=False, show_module_options=False, hash=[], delegate=None, no_s4u2proxy=False, domain=None, local_auth=False, port=445, share='C$', smb_server_port=445, no_smbv1=False, gen_relay_list=None,                \n                    smb_timeout=2, laps=None, generate_hosts_file=None, generate_krb5_file=None, generate_tgt=None, sam=None, lsa=None, ntds=None, dpapi=None, sccm=None, mkfile=None, pvk=None, enabled=False, userntds=None, shares=None, dir=None, interfaces=False, no_write_check=False,                       \n                    filter_shares=None, disks=False, users=None, users_export=None, groups=None, local_groups=None, computers=None, pass_pol=False, rid_brute=None, smb_sessions=False, reg_sessions=None, loggedon_users=None, loggedon_users_filter=None, qwinsta=None, tasklist=None,                            \n                    taskkill=None, wmi=None, wmi_namespace='root\\\\cimv2', spider=None, spider_folder='.', content=False, exclude_dirs='', depth=None, only_files=False, silent=False, pattern=None, regex=None, put_file=None, get_file=None, append_host=False, exec_method='wmiexec',                             \n                    dcom_timeout=5, get_output_tries=100, codec='utf-8', no_output=False, execute=None, ps_execute=None, obfs=False, amsi_bypass=None, clear_obfscripts=False, force_ps32=False, no_encode=False)                                                                                                   \n           DEBUG    Protocol: smb                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     netexec.py:138\n           DEBUG    Protocol Path: /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/nxc/protocols/smb.py                                                                                                                                                                         netexec.py:141\n           DEBUG    Protocol DB Path: /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/nxc/protocols/smb/database.py                                                                                                                                                             netexec.py:143\n           DEBUG    symmetric using \"pyCryptodomex\" for \"DES\"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         __init__.py:55\n           DEBUG    symmetric using \"pyCryptodomex\" for \"TDES\"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        __init__.py:55\n           DEBUG    symmetric using \"pyCryptodomex\" for \"AES\"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         __init__.py:55\n           DEBUG    symmetric using \"pyCryptodomex\" for \"RC4\"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         __init__.py:55\n           DEBUG    Protocol Object: <class 'protocol.smb'>, type: <class 'type'>                                                                                                                                                                                                                     netexec.py:146\n           DEBUG    Protocol DB Object: <class 'protocol.database'>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   netexec.py:148\n           DEBUG    DB Path: /home/pb/.nxc/workspaces/default/smb.db                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  netexec.py:151\n           DEBUG    Modules to be Loaded for sanity check: ['printnightmare', 'enum_ca'], <class 'list'>                                                                                                                                                                                              netexec.py:183\n           DEBUG    Loading module for sanity check printnightmare at path /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py                                                                                                                        netexec.py:190\n           DEBUG    Supported protocols: ['smb']                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  moduleloader.py:63\n           DEBUG    Protocol: smb                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 moduleloader.py:64\n           DEBUG    Loading module for sanity check enum_ca at path /home/pb/.local/share/pipx/venvs/netexec/lib/python3.13/site-packages/nxc/modules/enum_ca.py                                                                                                                                      netexec.py:190\n           DEBUG    Supported protocols: ['smb']                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  moduleloader.py:63\n           DEBUG    Protocol: smb                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 moduleloader.py:64\n           DEBUG    Creating ThreadPoolExecutor                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        netexec.py:45\n           DEBUG    Creating thread for <class 'protocol.smb'>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         netexec.py:48\n           INFO     Socket info: host=192.168.56.23, hostname=192.168.56.23, kerberos=False, ipv6=False, link-local ipv6=False                                                                                                                                                                     connection.py:177\n           DEBUG    Kicking off proto_flow                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         connection.py:239\n           INFO     Creating SMBv3 connection to 192.168.56.23                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            smb.py:579\n           DEBUG    Created connection object                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      connection.py:244\n           DEBUG    Performing authentication attempts...                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 smb.py:699\n           DEBUG    Port 135 is open, attempting MSRPC connection...                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      smb.py:703\n           DEBUG    Error while connecting to host: DCERPCException, which means this is probably not a DC!                                                                                                                                                                                               smb.py:709\n           DEBUG    Server OS: Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 10.0 build 14393                                                                                                                                                                                                                      smb.py:259\n           DEBUG    Error logging off system: Error occurs while reading from remote(104)                                                                                                                                                                                                                 smb.py:274\n           INFO     Creating SMBv1 connection to 192.168.56.23                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            smb.py:548\n           DEBUG    Update Hosts: [{'id': 17, 'ip': '192.168.56.23', 'hostname': 'BRAAVOS', 'domain': 'essos.local', 'os': 'Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393', 'dc': None, 'smbv1': True, 'signing': False, 'spooler': True, 'zerologon': None, 'petitpotam': None}]                             database.py:265\n           DEBUG    add_host() - Host IDs Updated: [17]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              database.py:275\n           INFO     Resolved domain: essos.local with dns, kdcHost: 192.168.56.12                                                                                                                                                                                                                         smb.py:299\n[15:09:49] INFO     SMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)                                                                                                                         smb.py:307\n           DEBUG    Trying to authenticate using plaintext with domain                                                                                                                                                                                                                             connection.py:498\n           INFO     Creating SMBv3 connection to 192.168.56.23                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            smb.py:579\n[15:09:49] INFO     SMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED                                                                                                                                                                                                smb.py:467\n           INFO     Loading modules for target: 192.168.56.23                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      connection.py:590\n           DEBUG    Supported protocols: ['smb']                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  moduleloader.py:63\n           DEBUG    Protocol: smb                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 moduleloader.py:64\n           DEBUG    Supported protocols: ['smb']                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  moduleloader.py:63\n           DEBUG    Protocol: smb                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 moduleloader.py:64\n           DEBUG    Calling modules                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                connection.py:250\n           DEBUG    Loading module printnightmare - <NXCModule.NXCModule object at 0x7ff1ab921940>                                                                                                                                                                                                 connection.py:285\n           DEBUG    Loading context for module printnightmare - <NXCModule.NXCModule object at 0x7ff1ab921940>                                                                                                                                                                                     connection.py:295\n           DEBUG    Module printnightmare has on_login method                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      connection.py:300\n           INFO     Binding to 'ncacn_np:192.168.56.23[\\\\PIPE\\\\spoolss]'                                                                                                                                                                                                                        printnightmare.py:43\n[15:09:50] INFO     PRINTNIG... 192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Failed to bind: SMB SessionError: code: 0xc0000022 - STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED - {Access Denied} A process has requested access to an object but has not been granted those access rights.                                   printnightmare.py:69\n[15:09:50] DEBUG    Closing connection to: 192.168.56.23   \n```\n\nOther modules that fail doesn't cause next module to not run:\n```\nnxc smb 192.168.56.23 -u '' -p '' -M enum_av -M enum_ca\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] essos.local\\: STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED \nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] SMB SessionError: code: 0xc0000022 - STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED - {Access Denied} A process has requested access to an object but has not been granted those access rights.\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [-] Error occurs while reading from remote(104)\nENUM_AV     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Found NOTHING!\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Active Directory Certificate Services Found.\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          http://192.168.56.23/certsrv/certfnsh.asp\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Web enrollment found on HTTP (ESC8).\n```\n\nIf `printnightmare` succeeds then other modules does run:\n```\nnxc smb 192.168.56.23 -u 'khal.drogo' -p 'horse' -M printnightmare -M enum_ca        \nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [*] Windows 10 / Server 2016 Build 14393 x64 (name:BRAAVOS) (domain:essos.local) (signing:False) (SMBv1:True)\nSMB         192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          [+] essos.local\\khal.drogo:horse (Pwn3d!)\nPRINTNIG... 192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Vulnerable, next step https://github.com/ly4k/PrintNightmare\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Active Directory Certificate Services Found.\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          http://192.168.56.23/certsrv/certfnsh.asp\nENUM_CA     192.168.56.23   445    BRAAVOS          Web enrollment found on HTTP (ESC8).\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nAll specified modules should run even though `printnightmare` fails.\n\n**NetExec info**\n - OS: Kali\n - Version of nxc: 1.4.0 - SmoothOperator - 8af4bfa6 - 816\n - Installed from: pipx\n\n**Additional context**\nMaybe this is related to #879 and #880. In this and the other bugs the order in which the modules are specified on the command line changes the behaviour of netexec.\n\nI'm not familiar with the codebase but it could have something to do with reusing connections.\n\n", "hints_text": "Easy fix for this, for some reason we are running `sys.exit(1)` on failure to bind which kills the thread instead of returning so more modules can run: https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/blob/40f572486ae06b0b94aede98ffa23414db71219e/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py#L70\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Easy fix for this, for some reason we are running `sys.exit(1)` on failure to bind which kills the thread instead of returning so more modules can run: https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/blob/40f572486ae06b0b94aede98ffa23414db71219e/nxc/modules/printnightmare.py#L70\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Pennyw0rth/NetExec/commit/0af6527f736385885a2e8dc37533810585cb2028"], "created_at": "2025-08-21T15:10:19Z"}
